The Falklands sit out in the South Atlantic Ocean; close to Argentina, but not geographically part of it. No-one, however, would think of Gibraltar as a separate territory if it didn’t have a border drawn around it. In purely geographic terms it is self-evidently part of Spain, so Spain’s argument from territorial integrity is much stronger than Argentina’s.
